      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence monitored with residual tolerance set to 1e-6 for force and displacement. Newton-Raphson iteration converged within 15 substeps for all load cases. No divergence or ill-conditioning warnings observed. Solver error contribution estimated < 0.1% of QoI values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by a second qualified analyst independent of the primary modeler. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material assignments verified against the documented simulation protocol. Peer review checklist completed and archived. No discrepancies found between intended and implemented model configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level2",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model with isotropic titanium alloy properties (Ti-6Al-4V) is well-established for static structural analysis of metallic implants. Contact between screw and vertebral body blocks modeled as frictional (mu=0.3) consistent with published literature. Model form assumptions documented and justified against ASTM F1717 test geometry and loading conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34 for Ti-6Al-4V) sourced from ASTM B265 and manufacturer material certification sheets. Geometry reconstructed from engineering drawings with dimensional tolerances documented. Input uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis; coefficient of variation for material modulus < 3%, geometric dimensions < 1%. Input parameter uncertainty propagated to QoI uncertainty estimates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). All constructs from the same production lot with material certification. Sample-to-sample variability characterized; coefficient of variation for stiffness 4.2%, yield force 5.1%. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration (10-degree angulation, standard block spacing). Only one test condition was evaluated, limiting the ability to assess model predictive capability across loading scenarios. This factor achieves Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; the shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given that the single condition directly maps to the COU and that all other factors meet or exceed requirements, maintaining overall Medium assurance level.",
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-noncannulated-f1717-accepted/factor/test-conditions"
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions mapped directly to ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and loading protocol. Block separation distance, screw angulation, and applied displacement rate in the FEA match experimental setup documentation. Equivalency table prepared comparing each simulation input to its experimental counterpart; no unresolved discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using the ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/uval. For stiffness: E/uval = 0.87 (< 1.96 acceptance threshold, percent difference 3.2%). For yield force: E/uval = 1.12 (< 1.96, percent difference 4.8%). For force at 40 mm: E/uval = 1.43 (< 1.96, percent difference 7.1%). All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds. Achieved Gradation 3 due to quantitative uncertainty-normalized metric application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
