      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to clinical performance of pedicle screw constructs. These QoIs are used by regulatory reviewers to assess structural adequacy. The mapping from simulation QoIs to COU decision QoIs is direct and documented in the simulation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
